Police in Jigawa State has busted a suspected armed robbery syndicate in Ringim Local Government Area of the state. Spokesman of the Jigawa State Command SP Abdu Jinjiri confirmed the development to DAILY POST. He said the incident occurred on Wednesday at about 0350hrs along Ringim to Dutse road. Jinjiri explained that Police rushed to the scene after they received intelligence report but the hoodlums took to their heels before the arrival of the police. He said the Police discovered that the hoodlums had abandoned one of their victims in a pool of blood and a motorcycle they robbed him. Jinjiri said the Police took the victim to a hospital for treatment and effort is on to arrest the fleeing suspects.